Churchianity is a negative description of [[organized religion]] that characterizes it as emphasizing the [[institution]]al forms of [[Christianity]] (traditions, rituals, committees, and programs) and omitting the actual [[gospel]] teachings of [[Jesus Christ]] that forms the basis of Christianity.

